verse.lines:
{lang-eng}Compared with Christ, in all beside
No comeliness I see;
The one thing needful, dearest Lord,
Is to be one with thee.
The sense of thy expiring love,
Into my soul convey;
Thyself bestow, for thee alone,
I absolutely pray.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Loved of my God, for him again
With love intense I’d burn;
Chosen of thee ere time began,
I choose thee in return.
Whate’er consists not with thy love,
O teach me to resign;
I’m rich to all the intents of bliss,
If thou, O God, art mine.{/lang-eng}
